
<section id="vectorialvectorial">
    <title>Operations Between two  Vectorial Signals</title>
  <para>
  These opcodes perform operations between two vectors, that is, each element of the first vector is processed with the corresponding element of the other vector.  The result is a new vector that overrides the old values of the source vector.
    </para>
    <para>
      Operations Between two  Vectorial Signals:
      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><link linkend="vaddv"><citetitle>vaddv</citetitle></link></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para><link linkend="vsubv"><citetitle>vsubv</citetitle></link></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para><link linkend="vmultv"><citetitle>vmultv</citetitle></link></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para><link linkend="vdivv"><citetitle>vdivv</citetitle></link></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para><link linkend="vpowv"><citetitle>vpowv</citetitle></link></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para><link linkend="vexpv"><citetitle>vexpv</citetitle></link></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para><link linkend="vcopy"><citetitle>vcopy</citetitle></link></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para><link linkend="vmap"><citetitle>vmap</citetitle></link></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para><link linkend="vaddv_i"><citetitle>vaddv_i</citetitle></link></para>
        </listitem>
